title: CATER 155253, Kly Mod 19-1: constant HVOCs.
text: Kly Mod 19-1: station HVOC's very hard with each trigger. All the red lites on the SCRTD light up with triggers. Lowered Eres from 5.8 volts. Opened compartment 3 and looked at EOLC circuit and pulse cable. Discovered the 2nd from the left EOLC 20 ohm current limiting resistor measures 6.5 meg ohms or so. The resistor electrodes are welded to the fuse clips. Removed resistor. Replaced upper fuse clip and installed new 20 ohm carbon film resistor. Was hoping that was the solve--no good. Still have hard HVOC's with triggers. Removed triggers: thyratron HV stands off with no triggers. Removed thyratron from spare station 01-8 next to 19-1. Last res volts recorded was 3.65. S/N = 100356. HV RTM from 01-8 = 53338 hrs. Installed thyratron in 19-1. Station comes up and runs well. Ranged thryatron to 3.84 volts. Very stable. DQ = 10 amps. KA = 287 mA. MM = 10.5%. Thyratron out = 300125. HVRTM = 45416 hours. CATER ready to close.

title: Some notes on investigating SXR intensity swimming
text: As observed earlier, the SXR FEL intensity has been drifting around with a period on the order of a couple minutes, without any comparable effect observed on the HXR line. The absence of any drift in the HXR FEL suggests that: (1) that the problem is not due to RF drift and (2) that the device is more likely to be off the common line, downstream of BLRCUS With this (admittedly questionable) intuition in mind, we investigated these devices/settings, but no smoking gun was found. * BC1 SXR IPK * BC2 SXR IPK * L1S SXR phase * L2 SXR AMPL * L3 SXR AMPL * LTUS feedback setpoints * UNDS feedback setpoints * laser heater temperature drift * UNDS phase shifter temperatures * BLRCUS/BRCUS temperatures & power supply It's possible the drift is due to a magnet with a poorly regulating BACT - unfortunately one might need to comb through them one-by-one to learn more...
